				<h2><img decoding="async" src="https://itfeelsgoodtobelost.files.wordpress.com/2018/06/dsc08268.jpg" alt="Local in Sapa" width="2894" height="2303" /></h2><p><br />Ha Long Bay, on the other hand, is impressive, specially if you go for an expensive company. Our boat was beautiful. The food was AMAZING. The activities are alright, but not breathtaking. A couple of hours kayaking and visiting a fisherman village. They also let us swim for 30 minutes in open water, which was nice. We missed being able to swim at some beach but this is forbidden by the government. Obviously, you have no independence as everything is planned.<br /><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text );"><br /></span></p><p><img decoding="async" src="https://itfeelsgoodtobelost.files.wordpress.com/2018/06/dsc08381.jpg" alt="The views were amazing" width="3600" height="2026" /></p><h4 style="text-align: center;"><b>Experience: Sapa wins by a little</b><b style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14px;"> </b></h4><h2><strong>Comfort</strong></h2><p>If you&#8217;re going to Sapa, be prepared to trek mountains, sleep in a maybe not very comfortable homestay, get muddy if it rains, etc. For Ha Long Bay, you literally feel like Paris Hilton and you don’t need to move a finger. Just relax and enjoy the cruise!</p><p><img decoding="async" style="color: var( --e-global-color-text );" src="https://itfeelsgoodtobelost.files.wordpress.com/2018/06/dsc08358.jpg" alt="Rafa in the boat" width="3600" height="2026" /></p><h4 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Comfort: very easy win for Ha Long Bay</strong></h4><p style="text-align: center;"><strong> </strong></p><h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2><p>If you have the time and the budget, do BOTH. Especially because both experiences are unique and are so different from each other. However, If we had to choose only one, <strong>we would choose Sapa, </strong>just because we had a really authentic experience, one of those that makes travelling so rewarding.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><em>What would you choose? Have you already been to any of the two? We would love to hear about your experience!</em></p><p><img decoding="async" src="https://itfeelsgoodtobelost.files.wordpress.com/2018/06/sapa6.jpg" alt="Sapa mountains" width="4800" height="2606" /><img decoding="async" src="https://itfeelsgoodtobelost.files.wordpress.com/2018/06/dsc08034-2.jpg" alt="Sapa in a sunny day is just too much" width="4800" height="2701" /></p>					</div>
